statement:
Consider the wave equation

\begin{align*}u_{tt} = u_{xx} , \,\end{align*} with initial conditions

\begin{align*}u(x,0) = f(x) = \begin{cases}
 2 \sin(2x) & 0 < x < \pi \\
 0 & \text{otherwise}
 \end{cases}, \;\; u_t(x,0) = 0.\end{align*}

(a) Suppose the domain is infinite, $-\infty < x < \infty.$ Write down
d'Alembert's solution, and sketch

\begin{align*}u(x,0), \; u(x,\pi / 4), \; u(x, \pi / 2), \; \text{and}\;  u(x, 3\pi/4) . \,\end{align*}
